		 Maestros of melodies																																	Classical Singers on Celluloid features documentaries made on the greatest classical artists to have lent their talent to the Hindi film industry. The legendary Siddheshwari Devis documentary made by Mani Kaul celebrates the life of exile, transgressing both home and dream. Gulzars film on Pandit Bhimsen Joshi is an attempt to capture the maestros secret of excellence. N.K.Issars film on Begum Akhtar portrays the many aspects of the personality of the Queen of Melodies. The portrait of Ustad Amir Khan, the legendary vocalist at his classical best, is etched by S.N.S. Sastry. Ustadjis personality, his family life and his music are also featured in this documentary. Through these films, some jewels of Indian music are being unfolded  as voices to remember and to treasure.					
